<!-- HOW TO CHOOSE -->
<section style="padding:6rem 2.5rem;background:#0A1A0A;">
  <div style="max-width:1200px;margin:0 auto;">
    <span class="lbl anim d1">Before You Sign</span>
    <h2 class="anim d2" style="font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif;font-size:clamp(1.8rem,4vw,3rem);font-weight:400;line-height:1.15;color:#F0FFF0;max-width:680px;margin-bottom:2.5rem;">
      How to Choose the Right One
    </h2>
    <div class="prose anim d3">
      <p>
        Not every fractional CMO is the right fit, and the wrong hire is expensive in lost quarters, not just fees. The single most common mistake is hiring a generalist when you need a specialist in your motion, or hiring a strategist when you actually need an operator. Get clear on which you need before you start interviewing.
      </p>
      <p>
        Use a structured process. Our guide to <a class="ilink" href="/how-to-hire-a-fractional-cmo">how to hire a fractional CMO</a> walks the full path, and <a class="ilink" href="/how-to-evaluate-a-fractional-cmo">how to evaluate a fractional CMO</a> gives you the scorecard. When you get to interviews, work from these <a class="ilink" href="/questions-to-ask-a-fractional-cmo-in-an-interview">questions to ask a fractional CMO</a>. And learn from other people's mistakes first: <a class="ilink" href="/5-mistakes-founders-make-hiring-fractional-cmos">the 5 mistakes founders make hiring fractional CMOs</a> will save you at least one of them.
      </p>
      <p>
        If your motion is specialized, we field operators who have lived it: <a class="ilink" href="/fractional-cmo-b2b-saas">fractional CMO for B2B SaaS</a>, <a class="ilink" href="/fractional-cmo-for-professional-services-firms">for professional services firms</a>, and <a class="ilink" href="/fractional-cmo-for-private-equity-portfolio-companies">for private equity portfolio companies</a>. And because every Treetop engagement is AI-native, your CMO arrives with the systems to run modern GTM: see the <a class="ilink" href="/ai-native-fractional-cmo">AI-native fractional CMO</a> model.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FAQ -->
<section id="faq" style="padding:6rem 2.5rem;background:#050D05;">
  <div style="max-width:820px;margin:0 auto;">
    <span class="lbl anim d1">FAQ</span>
    <h2 class="anim d2" style="font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif;font-size:clamp(1.8rem,4vw,3rem);font-weight:400;line-height:1.15;color:#F0FFF0;margin-bottom:3rem;">
      Frequently Asked Questions
    </h2>
    <div class="anim d3">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How do I get started with a fractional CMO?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Book a strategy call to discuss your GTM gaps, revenue goals, and team structure. We scope the engagement, set expectations, and outline the first 30 days. Most clients start within 1 to 2 weeks.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">What does it cost to hire a fractional CMO?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Most fractional CMO engagements run between $8,000 and $25,000 per month, billed as a flat retainer for 8 to 20 hours per week. The exact number depends on scope, team size, and how much execution you need versus pure strategy. For comparison, a full-time CMO costs $300,000 to $500,000 all-in per year once you add salary, bonus, equity, and benefits. See the full <a class="ilink" href="/how-much-does-a-fractional-cmo-cost">cost breakdown</a>.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">What is the typical contract structure?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">We offer flexible terms: 3 to 12 month engagements at 8 to 20 hours per week. You pay a monthly retainer based on scope and hours. There is no long-term lock-in. We prove value quickly or adjust the engagement.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">When can I expect to see results?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Strategic direction and team alignment happen within 2 weeks. Campaign launches and lead generation improvements show results within 60 days. Revenue impact depends on your sales cycle, typically 90 to 180 days.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Is a fractional CMO better than a marketing agency?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">They solve different problems. A fractional CMO is a leadership layer who owns strategy, sets direction, and manages your team or your agencies. An agency is an execution vendor for a specific channel. Most $5M to $50M companies need the leadership layer first, then point agencies at a clear plan. Here is the full <a class="ilink" href="/fractional-cmo-vs-agency">fractional CMO vs. agency</a> breakdown.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How do I know if I am ready to hire one?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">You are ready when marketing is driving revenue decisions but no senior person owns it, when you are about to spend on agencies or ads without a strategy, or when your team is busy but pipeline is flat. If you are pre-revenue or have no budget for execution, a fractional CMO is premature. The <a class="ilink" href="/signs-you-need-a-fractional-cmo">signs you need a fractional CMO</a> go deeper.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

